{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled a relatively modest sum and has demonstrated remorse and an attempt at restitution by partially paying back the funds. While the breach of trust inherent in an accountant's role is a serious aggravating factor, the lack of prior record and mitigating efforts suggest that a short custodial sentence is appropriate to serve as both a punishment and a deterrent without unnecessarily destroying the defendant's future employment prospects due to long-term incarceration. Six months is deemed sufficient to address the criminality of the act while reflecting the defendant's cooperation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
